Q: If there are 5,000 voters out of which 20% are not eligible to vote and there are two candidates contesting. The winning candidate won by 15% of the votes. What is the total number of votes he got?
Options: (a) 3267 (b) 2678 (c) 2797 (d) 2300 (e) 2781
